The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Wednesday, March 03, 2004  Corporate Briefs																								 HCL Infosystems has entered into a strategic alliance with European major Portwise under which the former will incorporate the latters software suite. HCL Infosystems has partnered with Portwise to launch HCL SecuAccess to provide secure remote access to partners, employees and suppliers over the network, a company release said.																								 iGate Global Solutions plans to increase its staff strength to 7,500-8,000 in the next two to three years. CEO Phaneesh Murthy said the company currently had about 3,200 professionals worldwide and was planning to more than double the strength in the next three years.																								 Tata AIG Life Insurance Company and United Bank of India have entered into a strategic bancassurance tie-up for distribution of Tata AIGs life insurance products to the bank customers across the country.																								 Sterling Biotech, a leading manufacturer of pharmaceutical grade gelatin, has posted a 112 per cent net profit at Rs 45.75 crore in the year ended December 31, 2003. Net sales in the reporting period have registered a 53 per cent growth at Rs 289.36 crore. ADVERTISEMENT
